# Getting Started with R, R Studio, and R Markdown

f **R code** *into* **LaTeX**, LyX, HTML, Markdown, AsciiDoc, and reStructuredText documents.


![Rmd logo][1]

>`R Markdown`  [rmarkdown.rstudio.com][2]

**R Markdown** documents are fully **reproducible**. Use a productive *notebook* interface to *weave* together narrative **text** and **code** to produce *elegantly* formatted output. Use multiple languages including **R**, Python, and SQL.


----------

![knitr logo][3]

>  `knitr`  [yihui.name/knitr][4]
 
**Knitr** is an engine for *dynamic report generation* with **R**. It is a package in the statistical programming language **R** that enables integration o

----------
----------


 `You will need to DOWNLOAD and INSTALL the following:`

>Note: they are all **FREE**


It is important to keep **R** and **RStudio** up-to-date. While it might be the case that you won’t have any issues with older versions, as packages are updated, you may receive strange errors. 

----------


![R logo][5]

1. `R`  [www.r-project.org][6]

      + Get the latest released version of FREE **Base R** from *CRAN*
        + the defaults are good...don't change them


----------


![R Studio logo][7]

2. `R Studio`  [www.rstudio.com][8]
 
      + Get the latest version of the FREE *Open Source* **Desktop Edition** of **R Studio**
        + the defaults are good...don't change them


----------


![LaTeX logo][9]

3. `LaTeX` 

     + Mac: [MacTeX][10]
         - Download (5+ min) to a folder and them double click on the PKG file and follow the installation instructions. 
         - You don't need to open anything after MAcTeX is finished installing.
     + Windows: [MikTeX][11] 
         - Pick the latest version of the **Net Installer**, not the Basic!  You need the full version 
         + 64-bit is better, if you have a 64-bit machine
         + When your **download** is complete, run the downloaded **installer**. Windows may ask you if you want to *“allow this app from an unknown publisher to make changes to your PC”*. If it does, make sure to click **Yes**!
         + This is the slowest part...


----------


For your enjoyment, [HERE][12] is a fun video about knitting.


  


